"**77.** See Cluver. Germania Antiqua, l. iii. c. 20. M. Freret, in the Mémoires de l’Académie des Inscriptions, tom. xviii. [The Franks were the descendants of the Sugambri and Chamavi and in the third century had been increased by the Chatti. The Amsivarii, Chattuarii, and some of the Bructeri also joined their “league.”]",

"**78.** Most probably under the reign of Gordian, from an accidental circumstance fully canvassed by Tillemont, tom. iii. p. 710, 1181.",

"**79.** Plin. Hist. Natur. xvi. 1. The panegyrists frequently allude to the morasses of the Franks.",

"**80.** Tacit. Germania, c. 30, 37.",

